      </div>
      <div class="pg-face pg-back">
        <span class="pg-name">Venus</span>
        <span class="pg-origin">PHOTOGRAPH — VISIBLE LIGHT</span>
        <p class="pg-note">Mariner 10 (1974), reprocessed 2020. In visible light you cannot see Venus's surface at all — only cloud tops. The famous orange "surface" images are radar, a different instrument answering a different question.</p>
